# Normalize line endings on commit. Without this, a contributor on Windows (or a tool
# that writes files with the platform default, which is how this got in) can commit CRLF
# and turn an edit of three lines into a whole-file rewrite — routes.py showed 1489
# changed lines in an 869-line file, which is unreviewable.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Never touch binaries.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.whl binary
